  [economy] F2P target: ~1 Sacred Log per day for active players (battle + daily + arcade). Never below this.
  [economy] Sacred Logs cannot be purchased directly — maintain prestige; only earned through gameplay
  [economy] [auto-fixer] public/markets.html root-cause themes: [added, lang, touchend, scripts, html] — 7x broken
  [economy] [auto-fixer] public/merch.html root-cause themes: [html, lang, merch] — 5x broken
  [emoji] Emoji regex must cover U+2B50 (star), U+200D (ZWJ), U+FE0F (variation selector), and U+20E3 (keycap) — these are outside the common ranges
  [regex] Never include quote characters in post-strip cleanup regex patterns — they match HTML attribute closing quotes and corrupt tag attributes
  [workflow] core.hooksPath=.husky — .git/hooks/ are ignored. All hook changes must go in .husky/ to be portable.
  [workflow] memory.json is always one commit behind in git but current on disk — post-commit writes it, next pre-commit stages it
  [workflow] Always run setup_github_environment BEFORE any git fetch/push/pull — token expires between sessions, never try unauthenticated first
  [workflow] When user asks a question, clarify intent BEFORE building — do not assume. Ask what they mean if ambiguous.
  [workflow] Before recommending a feature, grep/read the codebase to check if it already exists — read .nw-context inventory AND the actual files
  [workflow] Pre-commit hook blocks commits without .nw-session file and without at least 1 learning recorded — AI must follow CLAUDE.md startup checklist every session
  [workflow] [auto] ROOT-CAUSE FIRST: every fix commit MUST include root-cause in commit message. Protocol: (1) reproduce, (2) identify root cause, (3) fix, (4) verify coupled files.
  [workflow] SHIP COMMAND REQUIRED: Never manually git push + gh pr create + gh pr merge separately. Always use 'mycelium ship' which does auth→test→sync→squash→push→PR→merge atomically. The old workflow had two recurring failures: (1) auth token expires before push, (2) workflow stops after PR creation without merging.
  [workflow] VALUE GATE (mandatory): Before ANY multi-file change, answer in plain text: (1) What metric improves? (2) What bug is fixed? (3) What user-requested feature is added? If all three are NONE — STOP and tell the user 'this is cosmetic, should I skip it?' Never auto-proceed on refactors, reorganizations, or metaphor-driven restructuring.
  [workflow] NEVER claim something doesn't work without testing it first. When asked 'can X do Y?' — the answer is 'let me verify' not an assumption. Especially don't undersell to appear cautious — that's just as dishonest as overselling.
  [oracle] The OPENAI_API_KEY in .dev.vars and GENSPARK_TOKEN env var can expire — Oracle API falls back to 20 curated wisdoms gracefully. On Cloudflare production, set OPENAI_API_KEY and OPENAI_BASE_URL as secrets for live LLM responses.
  [oracle] Oracle fallback wisdom must follow the 5-part format: empathy opener, ancient consensus (Buddhism/Taoism/Bible/Quran), funny truth, actionable step, oracle seal. Never generic quotes.
