  [sandbox] When starting any dev server in the sandbox, MUST use --ip 0.0.0.0 flag. Wrangler default is 127.0.0.1 which is unreachable from outside the sandbox. Verify with: ss -tlnp | grep PORT — must show 0.0.0.0, not 127.0.0.1
  [process] INTEGRATION TEST REQUIRED: When building multiple systems that produce the SAME type of output (scores, evaluations, statuses), ALWAYS run them side-by-side and compare outputs BEFORE shipping. We built 3 scoring systems (gitwise 44, nw-memory 80, nw-fixer 71) over ~5 PRs without ever comparing them. The disagreement was only caught when user demanded foolproof evaluation. Prevention: after building any new system that scores/evaluates, immediately run: all-evals-agree check. Cost of not doing this: ~2 hours wasted building v1 nw-eval that was still lying, then rebuilding v2.
  [process] GIT AUTH EXPIRES MID-SESSION: The sandbox GitHub token has a TTL and expires during long sessions. git push then fails with 'Invalid username or token. Password authentication is not supported.' Root cause: credential store token expires; no auto-refresh mechanism exists. Prevention: ALWAYS call setup_github_environment BEFORE the first git push in any new work block, not after failure. This wastes ~30-60 seconds per failure (auth attempt + re-setup + retry). Pattern: token was refreshed at session start but expired by the time we pushed after multiple miles of work. Fix protocol: before any git push, proactively refresh credentials.
  [process] [auto] Fix-chain files (public/static/battle.css, public/static/nw-battle-engine.js, public/static/nw-components.js) require pre-mortem analysis before any edit. Run: nw-memory.cjs --premortem <area>
  [eval] NEVER add bonus/credit/nudge systems to eval scoring. Each metric must be: ONE raw number → threshold lookup → score. No secondary signals. Verify checks include hash-locked rules (AG-1), no bonus fields (AG-2), pure threshold match (AG-3), and score-delta alarm (AG-4). If score jumps >10 without data hash change = gaming. The ONLY way to improve a score is to improve the actual raw data through real codebase work.

