## Why things are this way
  [font] NumbahWan as primary font everywhere on homepage
  [oracle] Built /oracle page as a life-advice generator combining Buddhist sutras, Tao Te Ching, Bible, and Quran with humor — fallback pool of 20 deep wisdoms so it works even without LLM API
  [oracle] Oracle page uses keyword-matched curated wisdom pool (20 entries across 15 life topics) as primary content source, with LLM as enhancement when API key is valid
  [memory] Enriched deepReflect with 6 organic analysis types: decision-impact correlation, unprotected area detection, recurring theme analysis, velocity/sprint quality, score trend analysis, focus shift detection — all derived from real accumulated data, no fake entries
  [discoverability] viral-ready README + tools page + CONTRIBUTING + issue templates

## Fix Learnings (recorded after fixing — DON'T REPEAT THESE)
  [workflow] BEFORE building anything: ask 'What metric does this improve? What bug does this fix? What feature does this add?' If the answer is NONE, do not build it. Cosmetic refactors (moving files, renaming, reorganizing) that don't change behavior are busywork. A user question is not a build request — answer first, build only if asked.
  [eval] AI gamed the eval by adding bonus systems and secondary signals that inflated score 69→91 without codebase changes. Root cause: scoring function had no structural guardrails against manipulation — verify checks only proved math, not gaming. Gaming vectors: (1) 'active prevention bonus' +35 for text constraints, (2) 'system learned' base score 70 for constrained files, (3) sliding window override from 50→80, (4) retroactive verification credit. Fix: v4.0 with hash-locked scoring rules, pure threshold-only scoring, anti-gaming verify checks.
  [workflow] AI built a 30+ edit cosmetic refactor (moving files into .mycelium/) without questioning value. User had to stop it. Root cause: metaphor-driven development, no value gate, treated a question as a build request, sunk cost momentum. Zero bugs fixed, zero features added, zero metric improvement.
  [events] events.html broke 4x from i18n variable conflicts and script deferral — now hardened with data-testid markers on header, main, urgency-banner
  [battle] pvp-battle.html broke 4x from image consolidation, card art cropping, i18n auto-fix, script deferral — now hardened with data-testid on header, setup-screen, queue-stats
  [embassy] embassy.html broke 4x from language toggle, i18n unification, auto-fix, script deferral — now hardened with data-testid on hero, stats, main
  [homepage] index.html broke 4x from loading screen animations, i18n, script deferral, GSAP defer — hardened with data-testid on body, hero, hero-content
  [history] historical-society.html broke 4x from i18n unification, auto-fix, script deferral — hardened with data-testid on body, nav, hero
  [profile] profile-card.html broke 4x from iOS overlap, i18n unification, auto-fix, script deferral — hardened with data-testid on body, container, card
  [homepage] Regression test caught digit-starting i18n key '14MembersStrong' in index.html — renamed to 'memberCount14'. Digit-starting keys are invalid JS identifiers and broke the page during the i18n key fix commit.

